        Oh wow, so 'Lighter' is a 10/10 for you now? :D

        ACR stands for "Accelerated Chart Ratio", where if a song has been in the chart for at least 10 weeks & loses streaming for three consecutive weeks, the number of streams for it that count towards any subsequent charts are halved.

        Hence, this is why you see most songs take massive drops after 10-13 weeks on the chart, unless they're still selling incredibly well!

        Billboard's recurrent rules mean that songs are removed from the chart if...

        1) They have been on the Hot 100 for more than 20 weeks & are charting below #50.

        2) They have been on the Hot 100 for more than 52 weeks & are charting below #25.

        Exceptions are when a song gains in performance in the week it's due to go recurrent, but it'll be removed as soon as it declines!

        A song can still re-enter if it is recurrent, but it must satisfy both conditions stated above! Plus, radio airplay also counts towards to the Hot 100, rather than just sales & streaming (which I personally disagree with).

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (25/09/2020 - 01/10/2020)

        (Negative)

        1) 'Lighter' dropped out of the Top 5! I'm not at all surprised by this & I knew it was coming, but that doesn't mean I'm pleased with what's happened here.

        2) Take You Dancing is still going up! This better not become Savage Love: Part 2, but even then, at least that song had an addictive melody, not a hook that sounds like it could be from a horror movie, unlike this trash.

        3) Midnight Sky is back out of the Top 10! Yeah, Im still pleased it made it there at all, but her best song only gets two weeks in the region seriously?

        4) Laugh Now Cry Later leaving isnt good news either! Why are we letting this fall while Toosie Slide stuck around?

        5) Oh look, M Huncho is back with another completely forgettable dud! The production might be better than usual because its a lot more chill, but dude, how much more auto-tune do you need?!

        6) Incredibly, I only somehow just noticed this, but 'Fake Friends' is on ACR... yeah, way to put a damper on my Friday evening, you lot!

        (Mixed)

        1) Holy is the highest debut of the week, just about landing inside the Top 10, because well, its JB! Seriously though, going down the Christian route is a much better fit for Justin than any of the R&B stuff he did on Changes. He sounds very sincere here & the lyrics are rather sweet, but it wouldve sounded so much better without Chance The Rapper, as he just doesnt fit in well here at all!

        2) Lemonade is continuing its insane traction to finally reach the Top 10 & its showing no signs of slowing down either! Im starting to warm to the hook now, but I still feel nothing from the verses.

        3) What You Know Bout Love really came out of nowhere this week! Im still too obsessed with Mood Swings to have this on repeat for now, but its definitely got potential to grow on me.

        4) Loose took a huge drop this week! Its not on the same level as neither Rover nor Lighter are, but it still doesnt deserve to fall this far so early on.

        5) Come Over has some very pleasant production & Anne-Marie redeemed herself here, but I dont know, this is getting a low replay factor from me! Tion Waynes rap part is decent, but I just dont really remember much of it (maybe due to how short it is?). Its definitely cool to see it in the Top 40, but I dont think its going to grow on me any further unfortunately!

        6) 'Dance Monkey' fell back out again! I've always liked the song & I appreciate how unique it is, but it's just getting too old & overplayed to put into the "positive" section now, haha.

        7) Sadly, because Radio 1 are obsessed with it, Daisy is on the verge of breaking the Top 40! Thankfully, MGK could be about to make another chart appearance next week.

        8) As for the albums chart on one hand, Im pleased that the tributes to Pop Smoke were enough to take him to the top there! On the other hand, Ava Maxs album just had better music on it, so its a real shame that she wasnt able to get there despite leading all week.

        (Positive)

        1) Finally, Mood becomes big enough across all streaming platforms to take the #1! Its still a trap highlight for me in 2020 & the fact that it dethroned Wap makes todays chart all the more satisfying.

        2) As I predicted last week, Looking For Me is now officially the biggest EDM song across the country! I cant get this song out of my head & it just cheers me up every time I hear it, so Im perfectly happy with how big it has become.

        3) Lasting Lover takes a huge boost following a sales surge after the BGT performance & tons of radio airplay. Including mine, its at the top of the personal charts of four regulars here, so thats a very promising sign that itll get even higher!

        4) Following even more remixes, Dynamite is back on the rebound! Honestly, the original alone is enough for me its such a feel-good tune.

        5) Diamonds gets a reasonable debut & I think the radio are really going to love this song! The groove is on point here & the rest of the production fits Sams voice really well. I love the diamonds metaphor too!

        Thanks for reading everyone! Have a nice weekend. :)
